<span id="freeTextContainer9708775635716364256">&quot;Few things leave a deeper mark on a reader than the first book that finds its way into his heart. Those first images, the echo of words we think we have left behind, accompany us throughout our lives and sculpt a palace in our memory to which, sooner or later - no matter how many books we read, how many worlds we discover, or how much we learn or forget - we will return.&quot; - <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1232.The_Shadow_of_the_Wind__The_Cemetery_of_Forgotten_Books___1_' title='The Shadow of the Wind (The Cemetery of Forgotten Books, #1) by Carlos Ruiz Zafón' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Shadow of the Wind</a>, Carlos Ruiz Zafon<br/><br/>For me those enchanted pages will always be the ones in &apos;Unnikuttante Lokam&apos;.<br/><br/>I re</span>
  <span id="freeText9708775635716364256" style="display:none">"Few things leave a deeper mark on a reader than the first book that finds its way into his heart. Those first images, the echo of words we think we have left behind, accompany us throughout our lives and sculpt a palace in our memory to which, sooner or later - no matter how many books we read, how many worlds we discover, or how much we learn or forget - we will return." - <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1232.The_Shadow_of_the_Wind__The_Cemetery_of_Forgotten_Books___1_" title="The Shadow of the Wind (The Cemetery of Forgotten Books, #1) by Carlos Ruiz Zafón" rel="nofollow noopener">The Shadow of the Wind</a>, Carlos Ruiz Zafon<br /><br />For me those enchanted pages will always be the ones in 'Unnikuttante Lokam'.<br /><br />I read this book when i was in my 7th grade. I realize its influence during this second reading now, at the age of 25, and when i glance back into my life, i can see 'Unnikuttante Lokam'(Unnikuttan's World) entwined with mine. <br /><br />The goodness, the innocence that lasts in me might well be from this book.</span>
